00:19:18.730 --> 00:19:22.990 align:middle line:84%
Recall from earlier that one way
to create new neural networks

00:19:22.990 --> 00:19:28.450 align:middle line:84%
is by challenging our brain
with new inputs and tasks,

00:19:28.450 --> 00:19:33.940 align:middle line:84%
such as exposing
ourselves to new sounds.

00:19:33.940 --> 00:19:37.210 align:middle line:84%
Such as listening to sitar
music and the Indian ragas,

00:19:37.210 --> 00:19:40.360 align:middle line:84%
they were already
mentioned as one option.

00:19:40.360 --> 00:19:46.270 align:middle line:84%
We can also use variations
from standard musical tuning.

00:19:46.270 --> 00:19:51.390 align:middle line:84%
Examples include what we
call 432-hertz turning,

00:19:51.390 --> 00:19:54.730 align:middle line:84%
there's also something
called Pythagorean tuning,

00:19:54.730 --> 00:19:58.550 align:middle line:84%
and there's the Solfeggio
frequency tuning.

00:19:58.550 --> 00:20:01.420 align:middle line:84%
Now here, we're talking
about the frequency

00:20:01.420 --> 00:20:05.470 align:middle line:84%
of the music itself beyond
the brainwave states.

00:20:05.470 --> 00:20:07.750 align:middle line:10%
Most music in the
West is now tuned

00:20:07.750 --> 00:20:11.560 align:middle line:10%
to the note A is 440 hertz.

00:20:11.560 --> 00:20:14.680 align:middle line:84%
This is what we are
used to listening to,

00:20:14.680 --> 00:20:18.610 align:middle line:84%
and that our brains
are conditioned into.

00:20:18.610 --> 00:20:21.400 align:middle line:84%
But many sound healers
today are advocating

00:20:21.400 --> 00:20:24.490 align:middle line:90%
for 432 hertz tuning.

00:20:24.490 --> 00:20:27.100 align:middle line:84%
They claim that it is
a pure frequency that

00:20:27.100 --> 00:20:30.700 align:middle line:84%
is fundamental to the sacred
geometry and the mathematics

00:20:30.700 --> 00:20:32.690 align:middle line:90%
of the universe.

00:20:32.690 --> 00:20:35.650 align:middle line:84%
While I'm not a
musician, I've long

00:20:35.650 --> 00:20:39.340 align:middle line:84%
been interested in the
potential of sound and music

00:20:39.340 --> 00:20:43.270 align:middle line:84%
to be used for healing
purposes, so naturally, I

00:20:43.270 --> 00:20:48.430 align:middle line:84%
wanted to know more about
why they make this claim.

00:20:48.430 --> 00:20:52.520 align:middle line:84%
What's so special
about 432 hertz?

00:20:52.520 --> 00:20:56.950 align:middle line:84%
How does it relate to basic
sacred geometry and mathematics

00:20:56.950 --> 00:20:58.820 align:middle line:90%
of the universe?

00:20:58.820 --> 00:21:02.130 align:middle line:84%
To get beyond a
superficial answer,

00:21:02.130 --> 00:21:06.430 align:middle line:84%
it really required some digging
into the history of music.

00:21:06.430 --> 00:21:10.180 align:middle line:84%
In the late 17th century
France, under the rule

00:21:10.180 --> 00:21:17.260 align:middle line:84%
of the great King Louis XIV,
art in all its forms flourished.

00:21:17.260 --> 00:21:20.130 align:middle line:90%
King Louis XIV was a visionary.

00:21:20.130 --> 00:21:22.570 align:middle line:84%
He was a Mystery
School initiate,

00:21:22.570 --> 00:21:26.050 align:middle line:84%
and the creator of
the spectacular Palace

00:21:26.050 --> 00:21:27.580 align:middle line:90%
of Versailles.

00:21:27.580 --> 00:21:31.480 align:middle line:10%
There are many great musicians
who graced the royal court.

00:21:31.480 --> 00:21:34.600 align:middle line:84%
However, at the time
there was no agreed

00:21:34.600 --> 00:21:38.750 align:middle line:84%
upon standard for tuning
their musical instruments.

00:21:38.750 --> 00:21:41.900 align:middle line:84%
It seemed the different
musicians adopted

00:21:41.900 --> 00:21:44.710 align:middle line:90%
different tuning methods.

00:21:44.710 --> 00:21:49.180 align:middle line:84%
Around 1680, a physicist
and mathematician

00:21:49.180 --> 00:21:52.450 align:middle line:84%
named Joseph Sauveur
was brought in

00:21:52.450 --> 00:21:55.390 align:middle line:84%
to teach math and
astronomy to the princes

00:21:55.390 --> 00:21:57.940 align:middle line:90%
and pages of the royal court.

00:21:57.940 --> 00:22:01.930 align:middle line:84%
In 1689, he also became the
science and math teacher

00:22:01.930 --> 00:22:06.140 align:middle line:84%
to the king's nephew,
the Duke of Chartres.

00:22:06.140 --> 00:22:10.880 align:middle line:84%
He was then joined by the
music teacher, Etienne Loulie,

00:22:10.880 --> 00:22:15.470 align:middle line:84%
who instructed the duke and
the elements of music theory.

00:22:15.470 --> 00:22:18.170 align:middle line:84%
These two teachers
joined forces to show

00:22:18.170 --> 00:22:23.150 align:middle line:84%
how mathematics and music
theory were interrelated.

00:22:23.150 --> 00:22:25.700 align:middle line:84%
Together, they
worked for many years

00:22:25.700 --> 00:22:28.100 align:middle line:84%
on the science of
sound, which came

00:22:28.100 --> 00:22:31.280 align:middle line:84%
to be known later as
acoustics, a word that

00:22:31.280 --> 00:22:34.070 align:middle line:90%
means "able to hear."

00:22:34.070 --> 00:22:36.520 align:middle line:90%
Now what did they come up with?

00:22:36.520 --> 00:22:39.670 align:middle line:84%
They were able to
correlate musical pitch

00:22:39.670 --> 00:22:44.560 align:middle line:84%
with the frequency of sound
based on how many wavelengths

00:22:44.560 --> 00:22:47.440 align:middle line:90%
fit on a vibrating string.

00:22:47.440 --> 00:22:50.080 align:middle line:84%
They also studied what
frequencies harmonized

00:22:50.080 --> 00:22:53.050 align:middle line:84%
with each other,
as well as tuning

00:22:53.050 --> 00:22:55.870 align:middle line:84%
and working with other
musical instruments

00:22:55.870 --> 00:22:58.290 align:middle line:90%
and ranges of voices.

00:22:58.290 --> 00:23:02.770 align:middle line:84%
And from this research,
Sauveur developed a measure

00:23:02.770 --> 00:23:06.540 align:middle line:90%
of intervals within the octave.

00:23:06.540 --> 00:23:09.020 align:middle line:84%
The octave is a
natural phenomenon that

00:23:09.020 --> 00:23:12.410 align:middle line:90%
forms the basis of all music.

00:23:12.410 --> 00:23:16.370 align:middle line:84%
It is based on doubling
the frequency of sounds

00:23:16.370 --> 00:23:19.340 align:middle line:90%
as we go up each octave higher.

00:23:19.340 --> 00:23:22.250 align:middle line:84%
Within one octave in
our Western scale,

00:23:22.250 --> 00:23:25.190 align:middle line:84%
traditionally we have
seven major nodes.

00:23:25.190 --> 00:23:32.060 align:middle line:84%
Today, we know of these as
do re mi fa so la ti do.

00:23:32.060 --> 00:23:35.420 align:middle line:84%
The second do is twice
the frequency value

00:23:35.420 --> 00:23:41.000 align:middle line:84%
as the first do, and it
starts the next octave.

00:23:41.000 --> 00:23:43.490 align:middle line:84%
There are also
half-notes based on

00:23:43.490 --> 00:23:47.010 align:middle line:84%
fitting only
half-wavelengths on a string,

00:23:47.010 --> 00:23:52.220 align:middle line:84%
and this results in 12
subnotes in an octave.

00:23:52.220 --> 00:23:56.930 align:middle line:10%
In Sauveur's system, he
assigned the note of middle C,

00:23:56.930 --> 00:24:00.110 align:middle line:10%
which is the first node
on a keyboard sequence,

00:24:00.110 --> 00:24:04.190 align:middle line:10%
to be 256 hertz.

00:24:04.190 --> 00:24:06.320 align:middle line:10%
This would then
make the note of A,

00:24:06.320 --> 00:24:10.310 align:middle line:10%
which is the sixth whole note
or white key on the keyboard,

00:24:10.310 --> 00:24:15.300 align:middle line:10%
to be about 430.5 hertz.

00:24:15.300 --> 00:24:19.340 align:middle line:10%
And the reason for C
equals 256 hertz is again

00:24:19.340 --> 00:24:22.970 align:middle line:10%
based on the octave and
mathematical harmonics.

00:24:22.970 --> 00:24:29.660 align:middle line:84%
256 is perfectly divisible
by 8, and it is exactly

00:24:29.660 --> 00:24:33.860 align:middle line:90%
five octaves above eight hertz.

00:24:33.860 --> 00:24:37.110 align:middle line:84%
The Octaves of C thus
remain a whole number

00:24:37.110 --> 00:24:41.900 align:middle line:84%
in hertz, all the way
down to one hertz.

00:24:41.900 --> 00:24:44.900 align:middle line:90%
Now eight hertz is special.

00:24:44.900 --> 00:24:47.870 align:middle line:84%
It is a natural
frequency, and is

00:24:47.870 --> 00:24:51.290 align:middle line:84%
very close to the main
Schumann resonance

00:24:51.290 --> 00:24:56.780 align:middle line:84%
peak, which is the Earth's
electromagnetic heartbeat.

00:24:56.780 --> 00:24:58.490 align:middle line:84%
As we learned
earlier, eight hertz

00:24:58.490 --> 00:25:01.100 align:middle line:84%
is also the frequency
that marks that transition

00:25:01.100 --> 00:25:05.180 align:middle line:84%
between the alpha and the
theta brainwaves states,

00:25:05.180 --> 00:25:09.450 align:middle line:84%
and it's a number found
in the Fibonacci sequence.

00:25:09.450 --> 00:25:12.620 align:middle line:84%
So for all of these
reasons, Sauveur's system

00:25:12.620 --> 00:25:16.990 align:middle line:84%
is called scientific or
philosophical tuning.

00:25:16.990 --> 00:25:20.840 align:middle line:84%
Sauveur went even further to
try and break that octave down

00:25:20.840 --> 00:25:26.990 align:middle line:84%
into 3,010 parts based purely
on mathematical reasoning.

00:25:26.990 --> 00:25:30.170 align:middle line:84%
But as you can imagine, this
met with much resistance

00:25:30.170 --> 00:25:31.760 align:middle line:90%
from the musicians.

00:25:31.760 --> 00:25:35.240 align:middle line:84%
They argued that such
small differences cannot be

00:25:35.240 --> 00:25:38.810 align:middle line:84%
distinguished by the ear,
among other complaints.

00:25:38.810 --> 00:25:41.870 align:middle line:84%
Now because of this
backlash, his proposal

00:25:41.870 --> 00:25:47.724 align:middle line:84%
for a standardized scientific
system of tuning was rejected.

00:25:47.724 --> 00:25:51.990 align:middle line:84%
Now this story is a
good example of why

00:25:51.990 --> 00:25:57.090 align:middle line:84%
we must find a balance between
the art and the science

00:25:57.090 --> 00:26:01.480 align:middle line:84%
rather than elevating one
at the expense of the other.

00:26:01.480 --> 00:26:04.980 align:middle line:84%
What are other
alternative tuning skills

00:26:04.980 --> 00:26:08.280 align:middle line:84%
that sound healers and
alchemists are exploring

00:26:08.280 --> 00:26:10.870 align:middle line:90%
besides scientific tuning?

00:26:10.870 --> 00:26:14.760 align:middle line:84%
Well several are based on
the Solfeggio frequencies.

00:26:14.760 --> 00:26:17.280 align:middle line:84%
What are the
Solfeggio frequencies?

00:26:17.280 --> 00:26:20.340 align:middle line:84%
Well these are derived from
a more esoteric approach

